G3954  
παῤῥησία  
parrhēsia  
*par-rhay-see‘-ah*  
From [3956](g3956) and a derivative of [4483](g4483.md) *all* out
*spokenness*, that is, *frankness*, *bluntness*, *publicity*; by
implication *assurance:* - bold (X -ly, -ness, -ness of speech),
confidence, X freely, X openly, X plainly (-ness).  
